---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SectionHeading from "../components/SectionHeading.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="My Journey">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-24">
    <SectionHeading
      eyebrow="Narrative"
      title="My Journey"
      text="A personal reflection on how I became interested in human-AI research."
    />

    <article class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-8 text-slate-300">
      <p>
        I am interested in the space between humans and intelligent systems: how people think with tools,
        how interfaces shape behavior, and how AI can augment human capabilities rather than replace them.
      </p>

      <p>
        My path into this area comes from an interdisciplinary background in computer science and psychology.
        I care not only about building technical systems, but also about understanding how people use them,
        trust them, and adapt to them in real settings.
      </p>

      <p>
        At Grinnell, I want to explore this through research in human-centered AI, human-AI interaction,
        experimentation, and product thinking. I am especially drawn to questions about cognition, usability,
        decision-making, and the design of systems that genuinely help people.
      </p>

      <p>
        This page will eventually become a longer personal narrative in my own words, tracing the experiences,
        questions, and projects that shaped my interest in Human-AI.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
